WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.667 --> 00:00:05.601
♪♪

00:00:05.601 --> 00:00:09.334
SO THE MYTH IS, CAN A SURGICAL
LASER LIGHT A FART ON FIRE?

00:00:09.334 --> 00:00:10.901
Narrator:
AND TO GO FULL-SCALE,

00:00:10.901 --> 00:00:13.400
RACHEL, VALERIE, AND JESSE
ARE RE-CREATING

00:00:13.400 --> 00:00:17.601
AN ALL-TOO-ACCURATE
OPERATING-ROOM SCENARIO.

00:00:17.601 --> 00:00:19.000
WE ARE GOING FULL-SCALE,

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:20.367
AND THAT'S WHAT'S HAPPENING
BEHIND ME.

00:00:20.367 --> 00:00:22.934
OUR PATIENT HAS HAD
HIS CHEST CUT OUT.

00:00:22.934 --> 00:00:24.234
ON TOP OF THAT IS A SCREEN,

00:00:24.234 --> 00:00:26.367
AND ON TOP OF THE SCREEN
IS A BUNCH OF MEAT

00:00:26.367 --> 00:00:29.200
'CAUSE, YOU KNOW, OPERATIONS
INCLUDE A LOT OF MEAT

00:00:29.200 --> 00:00:30.501
IN THE FORM OF HUMANS.

00:00:30.501 --> 00:00:33.200
WE ARE GOING TO PIPE OUR FART IN
UNDERNEATH THAT MEAT

00:00:33.200 --> 00:00:34.267
SO IT AERATES UP THROUGH,

00:00:34.267 --> 00:00:35.467
AND WE'RE GONNA DRESS
ALL AROUND IT

00:00:35.467 --> 00:00:37.667
WITH A WHOLE BUNCH
OF SURGICAL TOWELS --

00:00:37.667 --> 00:00:40.801
THE MOST VIGOROUS FUEL
WE WERE ABLE TO TEST IN SCALE.

00:00:40.801 --> 00:00:45.300
HOPEFULLY THIS WHOLE PLACE WILL
BE ON FIRE IN A FEW MINUTES.

00:00:45.300 --> 00:00:47.200
Narrator:
SO THE TEAMS SCRUB UP,

00:00:47.200 --> 00:00:50.200
AND MASTER BUILDER JESSE
PLUMBS IN THE PATIENT

00:00:50.200 --> 00:00:53.000
TO RELEASE GAS
FROM THE INTESTINAL AREA,

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:55.868
SIMULATING AN ACCIDENTAL
COLON PUNCTURE

00:00:55.868 --> 00:00:59.300
AND PREMATURE EJECTION
OF FLATUS.

00:00:59.300 --> 00:01:02.901
NOW BUSTER'S JUST LIKE ADAM --
FULL OF FARTS.

00:01:02.901 --> 00:01:04.467
Narrator:
BUT UNLIKE ADAM,

00:01:04.467 --> 00:01:07.200
THERE'S NO RISK
OF BUSTER FAILING TO PERFORM

00:01:07.200 --> 00:01:09.033
WHEN THE PRESSURE'S ON.

00:01:09.033 --> 00:01:11.534
-YOU GOT ONE?
-I THINK SO.

00:01:11.534 --> 00:01:13.234
OH, IT'S A LITTLE,
TINY ONE.

00:01:13.234 --> 00:01:15.067
NO.

00:01:15.067 --> 00:01:17.701
NOTHING.

00:01:17.701 --> 00:01:21.567
Narrator: AND IN ADDITION TO THE
CONTROLLED INFLOW OF BACKFLOW,

00:01:21.567 --> 00:01:25.767
THE TEAM IS ADDING ONE
FURTHER INGREDIENT TO THE MIX.

00:01:25.767 --> 00:01:27.200
OXYGEN.

00:01:27.200 --> 00:01:30.167
EVERY OPERATING ROOM IS
AN OXYGEN-RICH ENVIRONMENT,

00:01:30.167 --> 00:01:31.701
SO WE'RE GONNA ADD OXYGEN
IN THE MIX

00:01:31.701 --> 00:01:33.501
AND SEE IF WE GET
A BETTER RESULT.

00:01:33.501 --> 00:01:36.234
Narrator: BUSTER'S MASK WILL BE
LEAKING OXYGEN,

00:01:36.234 --> 00:01:37.701
REALISTICALLY ENRICHING

00:01:37.701 --> 00:01:40.701
THE SOON-TO-BE COMBUSTIBLE
ENVIRONMENT.

00:01:40.701 --> 00:01:42.434
AND WITH
THE EXPERIMENTAL PLATFORM

00:01:42.434 --> 00:01:45.968
MATCHING THE MYTHICAL SETUP
AS ACCURATELY AS POSSIBLE,

00:01:45.968 --> 00:01:47.501
IT'S GO-TIME.

00:01:47.501 --> 00:01:51.033
ALL RIGHT. THIS IS CATASTROPHIC
OPERATING-ROOM FARTS.

00:01:51.033 --> 00:01:55.067
OKAY. I'M GOING TO
LOWER IN THE LASER.

00:01:56.701 --> 00:01:59.067
OKAY, LASER STARTING UP
IN 3...

00:01:59.067 --> 00:02:00.801
2...1.

00:02:03.200 --> 00:02:04.868
WE GOT FIRE
ALMOST IMMEDIATELY.

00:02:04.868 --> 00:02:07.200
-RIGHT.
-OKAY.

00:02:07.200 --> 00:02:09.300
TURN ON THE GAS.
COUNT IT IN.

00:02:09.300 --> 00:02:11.300
LETTING IT RIP
IN 3...

00:02:11.300 --> 00:02:13.200
2...1.

00:02:13.200 --> 00:02:14.200
[ LOUD BANG ]

00:02:14.200 --> 00:02:16.033
[ CHEERING ]

00:02:16.033 --> 00:02:18.133
-EXPLOSION!
-THAT WAS A THING.

00:02:18.133 --> 00:02:19.834
SOMETHING HAPPENED.
-SOMETHING HAPPENED!

00:02:19.834 --> 00:02:22.701
[ Laughing ]
THAT WAS REALLY COOL.

00:02:22.701 --> 00:02:25.167
[ LOUD BANG ]

00:02:25.167 --> 00:02:27.033
Narrator:
THE THERMAL CAMERA WILL REVEAL

00:02:27.033 --> 00:02:30.234
IF THE ADDITION OF THE OXYGEN
CAUSED AN EXPLOSION.

00:02:30.234 --> 00:02:32.968
THIS IS THE THERMAL.

00:02:32.968 --> 00:02:35.000
-OH!
-WOW.

00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:36.567
-OH, THAT WAS BIG.
-THAT WAS COOL.

00:02:36.567 --> 00:02:38.067
DO IT AGAIN.
DO IT AGAIN.

00:02:38.067 --> 00:02:39.534
Rachel: ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT.

00:02:39.534 --> 00:02:41.367
DID YOU SEE THAT?

00:02:41.367 --> 00:02:44.400
FIRE ENGULFED THE ENTIRE
PATIENT'S CHEST THERE

00:02:44.400 --> 00:02:46.601
FOR A SECOND.

00:02:46.601 --> 00:02:48.901
I MEAN, REALLY,
IF THAT HAPPENED,

00:02:48.901 --> 00:02:51.167
YOU'D RUN FOR YOUR LIFE.

00:02:51.167 --> 00:02:55.133
I MEAN, I WOULD CALL THAT
EXPLOSION.

00:02:55.133 --> 00:02:58.200
Narrator: BUT IS IT ENOUGH
TO CONFIRM THE MYTH?

00:02:58.200 --> 00:03:00.534
THIS ONE'S UP FOR DEBATE.

00:03:00.534 --> 00:03:01.834
HOW DO WE WANT TO
CALL THIS?

00:03:01.834 --> 00:03:04.534
PERSONALLY, I THINK
IT'S CONFIRMED.

00:03:04.534 --> 00:03:06.534
NO WAY.
I TOTALLY DISAGREE.

00:03:06.534 --> 00:03:07.767
THIS IS BUSTED.

00:03:07.767 --> 00:03:09.467
WE NEVER GOT OUR LASER
TO IGNITE OUR FART.

00:03:09.467 --> 00:03:11.434
WE ALWAYS HAD TO INTRODUCE
A NEW HEAT SOURCE.

00:03:11.434 --> 00:03:12.901
THAT'S A GOOD POINT.

00:03:12.901 --> 00:03:15.100
BUT OUR SETUP
IS TOTALLY REALISTIC.

00:03:15.100 --> 00:03:17.200
I MEAN, WE HAVE
THE MEDICAL-GRADE LASER,

00:03:17.200 --> 00:03:18.834
ADAM'S SYNTHETIC FART,

00:03:18.834 --> 00:03:21.033
AND THE OXYGEN
IN THE AIR AROUND IT,

00:03:21.033 --> 00:03:23.133
AND I TOTALLY SAW A FIRE.

00:03:23.133 --> 00:03:24.634
AND WE GOT A KABOOM.

00:03:24.634 --> 00:03:27.100
OKAY. GIVEN THAT WE DIDN'T
HAVE TO TRAVEL OUTSIDE

00:03:27.100 --> 00:03:30.467
THE CONFINES OF AN OPERATING
ROOM TO ACHIEVE THIS,

00:03:30.467 --> 00:03:31.834
I'M WILLING TO CALL IT
PLAUSIBLE.

00:03:31.834 --> 00:03:33.801
HOW DO YOU FEEL?
PLAUSIBLE IT IS.

00:03:33.801 --> 00:03:35.367
-PLAUSIBLE.
-PLAUSIBLE.

00:03:35.367 --> 00:03:37.901
ALL RIGHT.
LET'S GET THIS GUY TO THE O.R.

00:03:37.901 --> 00:03:41.067
[ SIREN WAILS ]

00:03:41.067 --> 00:03:48.234
♪♪

00:03:48.234 --> 00:03:50.100
THESE KIND OF STORIES
ARE TRICKY --

00:03:50.100 --> 00:03:52.300
ONES WHERE THE PREMISE
IS SENSATIONAL,

00:03:52.300 --> 00:03:55.601
BUT THE EXECUTION REQUIRES
THIS PERFECT STORM

00:03:55.601 --> 00:03:57.000
OF ALL THESE
DISPARATE ELEMENTS

00:03:57.000 --> 00:04:00.601
TO COME TOGETHER
TO CREATE THE CATASTROPHE.

00:04:00.601 --> 00:04:04.367
THEY'RE ALWAYS BUTT-KICKERS,
AND THIS ONE IS NO EXCEPTION.

00:04:04.367 --> 00:04:06.634
THE GUYS HAD TO GO DOWN
ALL SORTS OF WRONG TURNS

00:04:06.634 --> 00:04:07.934
TO GET TO THE FINAL RESULT,

00:04:07.934 --> 00:04:11.601
BUT THEY DID,
AND MY FINAL TAKEAWAY FROM THIS

00:04:11.601 --> 00:04:13.300
IS THAT MY FARTS
ARE STILL POTENT.

